you can launch the app and see logs by running `yarn release --logs`
for an automated end-to-end game, run `DEMO_GAME_LIMIT=1 yarn release --auto-solve` (builds, installs, auto-plays the demo playlist, exits on completion)
when analyzing an issue, you might want to add logs first with 'devLog' from 'src/utils/devLogger.ts' to see them
this mostly makes sense when testing logical functionality